article.description: Greg Tucker scored 15 points and Jacksonville State snapped a three game losing streak with a 74-60 win over SE Missouri State on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jacksonville St pulls away from SE Missouri St, 74-60
article.linkText: Jacksonville St pulls away from SE Missouri St, 74-60
article.story: CAPE GIRARDEAU, Mo. -- Greg Tucker scored 15 points and Jacksonville State snapped a three game losing streak with a 74-60 win over SE Missouri State on Wednesday night. JaQuail Townser added 13 points and Malcolm Drumwright finished with 11 points and seven assists for the Gamecocks (6-14, 2/3 Ohio Valley Conference), who won their first road game of the season. Jacksonville State shot 50.9 percent from the field and won the rebounding battle 35-27. The Gamecocks had a 10-0 run midway through the first half and led 38-23 at the break. DelFincko Brogan made a pair of free throws, JaQuail Townser hit a layup, and Christian Cunningham added another free throw to extend the Jacksonville State lead to 65-44 with 5:46 left. The 21 point margin was its largest of the night. Tony Anderson had 17 points for SE Missouri State (2-15, 0-5), which has lost five in a row.
